The Commodity Credit Corporation,CCC, has accepted a bonus offer from an exporter on the sale of75 head of dairy cattle to the Canary Islands, the U.S.Agriculture Department said.    The department said the bonus awarded was 1,459.00 dlrs perhead and was made to T.K. International Inc. It will be paid inthe form of commodities from the inventory of CCC stocks.    The cattle are for delivery during March-June, 1987, itsaid.    An additional 3,925 head of dairy cattle are stillavailable to the Canary Islands under the Export EnahcnementProgram initiative announced July 28, 1986, it said. Reuter&#3;